headline: Musk targets costly fleet of Lockheed Martin’s F-35 fighter jets, FT reports
summary: Elon Musk, charged with cracking down on waste across the U.S. federal government, has recently targeted the Pentagon’s costly fleet of F-35 fighter jets, Sylvia Pfeifer of The Financial Times reports. Musk has spent the past few weeks mocking the Lockheed Martin (LMT)-built aircraft on social media, which has fueled the discussion on whether piloted fighter jets are needed when budgets are pressured and increasingly sophisticated drones are being successfully deployed. Published first on TheFly
